  "text": "It has been shown that the emotional connotation of words can influence both the processing of those words (see, e.g., [CITATION_1] ) and the re-enactment of movements related to them [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In this work, we compared the time of mental reactivation of sense-related experience rated as causing more or less pleasant and unpleasant emotions.",
